,Recommended,239120,12284844,"Posted: 28 September, 2014",all,OnionKnight1994,"My favorite game of all time. The story and characters aren't particularly deep, especially compared to later games in the series, but deep Job Class-based gameplay, a healthy challenge, plenty of varied locations, and an excellent soundtrack (my personal favorite) all help this game hold up well even today. Despite its short length compared to other Final Fantasies and a slight emphasis on grinding, Final Fantasy III stands tall among the typical turn-based RPGs. Some people, myself included, think it stands at the very top."
