,Recommended,239120,17998416,"Posted: 12 September, 2015",all,fruitbatsalad,"I loved this game on the DS, so I bought it again here.  I highly recommend it if you're a fan of old school JRPGs with random encounters and turn-based battles.The story is simple, but you have to remember that this is a remake of a game from 1990.  For me, a big part of the appeal is the character customization.  There are dozens of ""jobs"" (character classes) which you can switch to at any time once you've unlocked them.  Even though the story proceeds in a linear fashion, the character customization gives you a lot of freedom to do what you want - so you have nonlinear choices in that regard.The DS version had very low resolution graphics, and it's refreshing to play on a big screen with sharp visuals.  After playing this, I don't think I can go back to the DS version.  Keep in mind that these are still the original low-polygon models.  Personally, I find the low-polygon look to be charming, but some people might not like it.I've played a lot of games including many RPGs, and this has possibly the best soundtrack I've ever heard in a game.  Yes, even when comparing it to other great soundtracks like Chrono Trigger/Cross and other Final Fantasy games.  The remade FF3 soundtrack is that good.  I recommend headphones to get the full experience."
