,Recommended,239120,25403386,"Posted: 7 September, 2016",all,TribalSage,"For those not aware this is not the Final Fantasy III that came out for the Super Nintendo, that was actually part VI. This is the real Final Fantasy III that wasn't released in the USA till many years later.This is a great old school turn based Final Fantasy game that continues the epic story about the Warriors of Light. There's a total of 9 playable characters with likeable stories and dialog. This the Final Fantasy that introduces the job system to the series. There's 23 different jobs and any character can use whatever job they like. There's over 200 different enemies/bosses to battle which you will be able to check with the help of the Bestiary, which is a menu that lets you see all the characters you've fought as well as show a record of achievements. There's also a nice variety of armor, items and weapons which include the awesome Legendary items(10 armor and 13 weapons). Like all old school RPGs it's a bit of a grind especially to get the Legendary items but if you played old school RPGs you know this already. Overall it's another great game in the series and I do recommend it.While I do recommend the game because it is a good game it does have some game breaking bugs which can occur. That doesn't mean they will, but if they do happen don't be surprised. I did unfortunately suffer a game breaking bug on my playthrough. After about 60 hours into the game the Crystal Tower reset and I lost my airship. So there was no way to leave the area and I couldn't progress through the tower because I didn't have the items to unlock it anymore. Square Enix needs to address these issues."
