,Recommended,239120,16460782,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Arsene-Lupin,"The best way to play Final Fantasy III? The Nintendo DS remake.The next-best way to play Final Fantasy III? The PC port of the Android port of the DS remake--in other words: this.There are three facts you need to be aware of:1. Final Fantasy III, like most of the old Square and Enix games pre-dating their unfortunate merger, is an absolute classic.2. This game is a remake of Final Fantasy III. A true remake, not a port/update/remaster/whatever new marketing term people are using to pretend lazy ports are better than they are.3. But it's also a port, ya' know? And not a very good one. I'm not sure, but it may in fact simply be running the Android version remulated. Want the game to display 16:9 at 1080p? Sure, you can select that in the options menu--you can select lots of stuff--but no matter what you select, you get a letterboxed game screen. Want a smooth, 60fps framerate? Haha, no. Willing to settle for simply a smooth framerate? Sorry, but still no. The game is locked at 30fps and will frequently dip below that in combat. We're talking 24-28fps stuttering depending on how fancy the combat animation is.Final Fantasy III is a classic game, and that counts for a hell of a lot. And if you want to play the game on a big (at least relatively speaking) screen, the only ""legitimate"" (read: legal) way to do so is to buy this particular port. Otherwise the best option is the NDS original (the original remake, not the original NES game)."
