76561198051032319,Recommended,239120,15021105,"Posted: 23 March, 2015",all,Mad_Tyrion,"TLDR : Buy this game if you wanna deep dive in an old-school rpg.If you like the old-school turn based combat system you won't be disappointed with this one.The game itself offers a lot of variation in terms of playstyle in combat, as there's over 20 jobs any character can have that are unlocked while you progress throught the game, but as long as you don't swap those around too much you won't need to grind at all to complete the main story. The only thing that requires real grinding is the secret boss, but that's pretty much to be expected. That said i personally found the game quite easy, except for the last dungeon which ends up being quite interesting. Also beware that while it has an awesome soundtrack, there is no real deep story, no voice actors and the graphic is quite old. So in the end i really recommend this if you know what you are buying, as it's one of those games that ain't really for anyone."
,Recommended,239120,14550406,"Posted: 19 February, 2015",all,Freebird,"Turn-based RPG, before the days of the active time battle, there were the originals, this is a remake of Final Fantasy III originally released exclusively in Japan for the ""Family Computer"" ... That's how old the mechanics/storyline are. HOWEVER, there have been quite a few tweaks made to bring it up to date with what you would expect of a good RPG ... In the 90's. As far as storyline goes, it's pretty bland and generic. Collect the crystals, beat the bad guys, save the world. It does have some hidden humorous elements in it, but they're few and far between. This game is badly dated, but it's still a solid essential for a Final Fantasy fan, and it is enjoyable up to about level 40, when the grind from 40-60 begins, it will take you about three hours on a good day, and you pretty much need to be 60 to beat the game. DO NOT go into this game thinking you will 100% every aspect of it, and if you do, for the sake of sanity, make sure you kill every sea creature while you still have your sea boat, or you'll be SOL for getting that beastiary achievement. You will not want to replay this game. Sad but true, it's just not that immersing compared to later Final Fantasy games.There are no voiceovers as seen in FFIV, there are summons, which are cool.TL;DRGrindfest, random-battle hell, old-school level up, good world maps, sometimes even surprising, bosses are not overly frustrating (There is no boss in this game that will one-shot your entire party* like later Final Fantasy games), bland storyline, decent graphics, decent amount of secrets. Overall a B- as far as RPGs are considered. There just isn't much to this game to compare with newer titles.*There is a boss that will one shot your party, but it is meant to happen, there is no way out of it, don't freak when it does happen."
