,Not Recommended,239120,20184895,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,ZiChann,"Note: This is just a problem with the Steam port of this game.Although the experience is almost identical to the experience that you would receive playing this on iOS, there's a major problem with this port that iOS doesn't have. No matter where you are in the game, your story progress can be ultimatelyresetback to the starting town, Ur. You'll have to go through the whole story once again with three of the four characters going back to level 3/4. (Un)Fortunately, Luneth keeps his level, you keep all your items/spells, and all characters keep their job levels and current jobs.If you still wish to buy this game, or have already bought it and are reading reviews after buying a game, just be sure to save frequently, but save carefully. If at any time you notice that your job icon isunavailable, fall back to your last save. If the job icon can't be chosen, it means that your game has been set back to the beginning of the storyline.If you have a Nintendo DS or iOS device, or even a NES, I'd just recommend you buy it for that hardware to avoid this flaw."
