,Not Recommended,239120,11682260,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,BlueMagican,"While I like the fact that Squre Enix is attempting to let people play games that they may not have had access too in the past this game sufferes from one critical flaw which to me makes it pointless to pay for... even 2 cents is too much for it.  Before I go into the negative aspects though let me touch on some of the positives.  This game has many good things going for it, the first of which I already mentioned, its a game that alot of folks never had access too.Next its based off fo the Nintnedo DS/PSP rerelease of the game, which orginially was on the Nintendo Entertainment System (well techinically the Famicom but alot of folks dont know what that is) so don't expect the new combat styles of say Final Fantasy XIII.  This is classic old school Final Fantasy goodness... and the basis of which you see reflected in many future games.  Some things such as the job system are still seen feflected in the modern games.  The graphics are nice, though the font is a little ugly, the music as always is beautiful.What kills this game completley for me is are simple things that Square Enix could fix and in fact I've contacted Square Enix about and they dont really care about them.  If you are playing the game with and I mean this litterally, ANY NON MICROSOFT 360 WIRED CONTROLLER then the game will lock up and freeze on you.  I worked with Square about this and their solution was to unplug my Mad Catz Wired Xbox 360 controller and plug in a Microsoft branded one.  Though playtesting I can confirm that even having the controller plugged in but not in use crashes the game.Edit:  I can confirm that a wired Xbox 360 controller works just fine.  For anyone curious as to why the Microsoft 360 Wireless controller doesn't work, its because it requires Bluetooth, even when pluged in using an USB adapter.  All the USB adapter does is charge the controller it doesn't acutally function as in the same way a wired controller does.So in short they don't want you to pay 15 for the game.  They want you to pay 15 for the game, and approximately 40 for the controller makeing the cost of this Final Fantasy game 55 dollars.  (Edit:  You can now find the controllers for around 25 dollars on sites like Amazon, but still its an unstaded addtional cost if you want to use a controller.)  Yes I could play the game with nothing plugged in but as someone who plays a lot of diffrent games on my cast this isn't very reasonable, plus Final Fantasy Games just don't feel right being played with a keyboard.  (Edit:  In addition as many people who have problems with carpal tunnel have pointed out using a controller is much easyer on them ta hen using the keyboard.)In short the cost of this game is 55 bucks.... I can go buy a brand new Triple A title game for that much.  I'd rather just get this while its on sale on PSN (which happens fairly regularly) or get a modded DS so I can play my DS version.  Avoid at all costs untill fixed IMHO.Edit:  Since I can now post a longer version of this I wanted to expand my review.  Another problem with this veresion of the game is that it has many bugs.  One of which is a fatal game flaw in which if characters die you can lose all your progress.  By this I mean you can lose the abilitiy to change jobs, your ships/boats which are required for travel, and other simular bugs.This has since been verified by a caster I have a great amount of respect for: Crumps2 who is currently (as of 12/4/14) playing though all the Final Fantasy games on Twitch.tv.  This has caused him and Cereth the other caster that is playing though all the games to acutally ABANDON this game untill such time as they can get modified Nintendo DS systems to be able to play the game.  Once again, buy at your own risk."
