,Not Recommended,239120,18152575,"Posted: 22 September, 2015",all,Rick,"Final Fantasy III is an unrewarding grind with a so-simple-it's-convoluted story reminiscent of Kingdom Hearts'.  The story is about the balance between light and darkness--and the game lectures and reminds the player about this balance a few hundred times throughout, as New Age-plagued JRPGs often do.Its gameplay is where it fails on virtually every level: Most of the jobs are useless, half the abilities in the game are bugged and simply don't work, and players will lose hours upon hours of progress due to a complete absence of in-dungeon save points.  You can only save on the world map, and some dungeons are 5+ hours long.Even players who only desire a peek at the advent of Final Fantasy's Job System will be disappointed, as the game's combat shoehorns players into a select few jobs, rendering the remainder not only unusable, but boring and uninspired as well.  For example, over half of the game's jobs are mere upgrades to existing jobs, offering nothing of substance on a gameplay level.The music and graphics are sometimes surprisingly good.I recommend this game to hardcore completionists and to Final Fantasy XIV fans who want to see the origins of the ""Crystal Tower"" raid.  To anyone else: don't waste your time.  Final Fantasy III is just not good enough to justify the time investment."
