in job and almost don't get any support at all. This made it even harder to play certain jobs and which made me change back to other jobs just to be able to pass some areas. That resulted in me having to farm to get back the exp i lost while playing as another job. It was either that or playing as an almost usless charachter that made ruffly a third (or less) of the damage my teammates did.Now get me right, i'm not agains farming. It's a great way to stay one step before the game, dedecating time to making your playthrough easier/funnier. But when the game requieres you to farm to progress, it's just get's boring.This formula repeated itself several times and at this point i did not enjoy playing it anymore and just gave up on it.I whould not recommend playing this game, i felt like it made it hard and boring to play certain parts of the game when i really should be fun and exciting. Not everything about this game is bad, heck, most thing are pretty good. But it wasn't enought for me to keep playing it."
