76561198037667625,Recommended,239120,14395843,"Posted: 8 February, 2015",all,Wolfinator,"A remake of an old NES classic that was only released in Japan for the 'Famicon' (their version of the NES). The story progression stays 100% the same with added vibrancy to the beginning to give the characters more depth than the original. The difficulty has been tweaked to attain somewhat of an easier feel. The original was very grindy, but they've removed a little bit of that in the first few levels of XP. They added in a few extra quests at end game to ascertain a level of difficulty of the original with a new boss that takes a lot of grinding to be able to stand a chance against, which is what every FF fan deserves at the end of a long haul of the game. They kept the buy in bulk discount which is great, especially at the beginning when gil is somewhat scarce unless you grind a bit for that. I'd recommend this game to any RPG fan who hasn't played the original or the DS remake for those that love a good solid story with improvements to an already awesome classic."
