,Recommended,239120,28753763,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,joshbittner23,"This game is hard! No save points in dungeons, so the endgame is one heck of a gauntlet to run. Also character deaths in battle is a lot more unforgiving cause you can't buy Phoenix downs or elixirs, either. Without spoiling anything, there are also some parts of the game where you will be forced to change your party's jobs into a mage team, too. Finally, you -will- have to grind a lot in this game. Like, significantly more than later games in the series, which also disguise some of their grinding with side quests and other content rather than just a massive enemy difficulty spike when you set foot in a new area.The story is a lot more sparse, but it's okay. Final Fantasy 1-3 didn't really have much in the way of stories. I wouldn't recommend it as a starting point for getting into the series (unless you just want to start with arguably the most difficult title and can get through the increased amount of battle difficulty and grinding in the game), but once you've played some of them, it's worth checking out."
