76561198035192891,Recommended,239120,31145724,Posted: 14 April,all,midgkahn,"Let me start by saying I'm a bit biased, I've been a fan of the series for decades. I first played III on the DS, so this port felt familiar and comfortable to me. I like having the wide variety of classes and true to the series nature you're looking at a good 40 to 60 hours for a play-thru.There aren't many things I see wrong with it but I'll list what I didn't care for. I save a lot as I play rpgs, so being limited to 3 save slots was tough on me. The game at points isn't always the clearest about where to go next, but I expect that of rpgs. Lastly, be careful of switching jobs in an area you just arrived. I did that once or twice and was stuck struggling to raise my level so that I could survive the new area.Overall I would really recommend it, and it's a great way to start the series since there's no big, complex story behind it. You can pick up/stop and not have too much difficulty in knowing what is going on. One last bit, it's controller friendly, but in my opinion setting the key inputs for awsd layout works great."
